2026-04-16 | Minimum Distance to Same Element in Circular Array

	Question
Return array of answers for all queries.

	Approach
1.	Store indices of each value:
		value → sorted list of indices  

2.	For each query:
		let idx = queries[i]  
		value = nums[idx]  

3.	If only one occurrence → return -1  

4.	Use binary search on index list:
		find position of idx  

5.	Check neighbors:
		previous occurrence  
		next occurrence  

6.	Compute circular distance:
		dist = min(|i-j|, n - |i-j|)

7.	Take minimum  

	Time Complexity
	O(n + q log n)

	Space Complexity
	O(n)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> minDistance(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& queries) {

        int n = nums.size();

        unordered_map<int, vector<int>> mp;

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            mp[nums[i]].push_back(i);
        }

        vector<int> ans;

        for(int q : queries){

            int val = nums[q];
            auto &v = mp[val];

            if(v.size() == 1){
                ans.push_back(-1);
                continue;
            }

            int pos = lower_bound(v.begin(), v.end(), q) - v.begin();

            int res = INT_MAX;

            // previous
            int prev = v[(pos - 1 + v.size()) % v.size()];
            int d1 = abs(q - prev);
            res = min(res, min(d1, n - d1));

            // next
            int next = v[(pos + 1) % v.size()];
            int d2 = abs(q - next);
            res = min(res, min(d2, n - d2));

            ans.push_back(res);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
For each value:
		only nearest neighbors in sorted index list matter  

Using binary search:
		we efficiently find closest occurrences  

Circular distance handled via:
		min(|i-j|, n - |i-j|)
